{
  "texts": [
    "That is, papers cited 16 times or fewer are categorized as having low scientific potential, while those cited more than 16 times are classified as having high scientific potential.",
    "Second,our moving time windows are simplified because, with scientific citations, we do not face the truncation issues that we faced with patent renewals.",
    "We train 21 models and truncate academic citations to the focal year, but in this case, the window used for training is t -10 to t -1.",
    "These models perform satisfactorily, with an average accuracy and AUROC of 0.71.",
    "We provide more details on the methodology and performance of these models in Online Appendix A.3.2."
  ]
}